23361.content: Is FDA aware of the current {drugName} shortage and its possible causes?
23361.name: Dialogue State

23364.content: Yes, we are aware. Basically, the shortage has been triggered by a range of factors including a reported impurity in sample test results.
23364.name: Dialogue State

25752.content: From now on, you're no longer training.
25752.name: Dialogue State

25760.content: You did well, but we have faith in you that you can do much better when you have to deal with real patients!
25760.name: Dialogue State

25886.action_text: URGENT: DRUG RECALL Dear Kate, This is to inform you of a drug recall involving {disruptionSize} units of your drug inventory. This recall has been initiated due to a reported impurity in some products including {disruptionSize} units that we distributed to you before. Immidiately quarantine this amount in your inventory and return them. This recall is being made with the knowledge of the Food and Drug Administration. Sincerely,

25891.content: We initiated a recall from companies and medical centers. Many of them have received our recall notice and the rest will receive it shortly.
25891.name: Dialogue State

25892.content: We're talking live to one of the FDA representatives about the ongoing shortage.
25892.name: Dialogue State

26010.content: Hey Kate! This is Bob. Can you come and see me in the ER?
26010.name: Dialogue State

26016.content: This is your boss you're talking to!
26016.name: Dialogue State

26065.content:
That was a lot of information I received last week. 
And they call this a game?!
26065.name: Dialogue State

26067.content: Who do they really think I am to take in all that information? 5 Professors', 4 PhDs' and a Postdoc's spirits in one body?!
26067.name: Dialogue State

26069.content: I like my boss, he's nice.
26069.name: Dialogue State

26070.content: This  photo frame is dull! I have to change this sometime next week.
26070.name: Dialogue State

26073.content: Now it's a bright photo frame. love this picture!
26073.name: Dialogue State

26077.content: Now the clock is running! and I'm here at 8 AM sharp. Time is precious, so is sleep!
26077.name: Dialogue State

26078.content: Another day at work! I want to make a difference today! No, not again with the photo frame or the batteries. A difference from inside!
26078.name: Dialogue State

26097.content: Did you notice that the clock didn't work this whole time?! I should get some batteries for that too.
26097.name: Dialogue State

26103.content: I guess I kinda had a dream, but I don’t want to talk about it!
26103.name: Dialogue State

26104.content: I like this job. Nothing makes you feel better than saving lives.
26104.name: Dialogue State

27389.action_text: Proportional to the number of all patients This means that if there are not enough units in the inventory to treat all patients, available units are proportionally allocated among urgent and non-urgent patients.

27393.action_text: Prioritize urgent patients This means that all of the urgent patients will be treated first, and if there are any units left in the inventory, non-urgent patients will be treated.

27403.action_text: Order based on reliability The total order amount will be divided proportionally between suppliers based on their reliablity percentage which is the number of times that orders have been fully satisfied in the past 10 weeks.

27407.action_text: Order equal amount The total order amount will be divided equally between suppliers.

27475.action_text: If you are concerned about suppliers' reliablity in delivering orders on time, you may want to order more than suggested amount to ensure that you can satisfy patients demand.

27484.action_text: If you expect demand to change significantly in the future, you may wish to increase or decrease the order amount.

27493.action_text: If you are concerned about inventory costs, you may want to order less than the suggested amount to decrease inventory costs.
